meanings.definition: To give more blessings than someone else.
meanings.sent1: She outblesses her friends by always sharing her snacks.
meanings.sent2: He always outblesses others with his kind words and deeds.
meanings.sent3: The generous neighbor seemed to outbless everyone in the community.
meanings.sent4: Her positive energy outblesses any negativity around her.
meanings.sent5: The sun outblesses the clouds, shining brightly on the earth.

meanings.definition: The act of receiving more blessings than someone else.
meanings.sent1: Her outblessing brought her much joy and gratitude.
meanings.sent2: The unexpected outblessing made her day brighter.
meanings.sent3: His outblessing from the universe felt like a warm hug.
meanings.sent4: The outblessing of good fortune seemed to follow her everywhere.
meanings.sent5: The outblessing of love filled her heart with happiness.
